Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) Senior Tennis Championship Men’s Singles defending champion Emmanual Sylvester yesterday continued his campaign  on a winning note after seeing-off Joshua Daniel 6-2, 6-0 to advance to the 3rd  round. Sylvester had on Monday started the defence of his crown on a good note by stopping UK-based  Andu Muktar 6-2, 6-3 in the championship’s opener. Tournament seed 3, Similarly, 3rd seed Abdulmumuni Babalola booked his 3rd  round ticket with a  convincing 6-1, 6-3 victory over Michael Ayoola.  Meanwhile, actions are equally hitting up in the CBN Women’s Singles  as former two-time champion but unranked Sarah Adegoke eliminated Salamatu Haruna, 6-1, 6-0 while number two seed  Christie Agugbom edged Jumai Mohammed  6-3, 6-1. Women’s Singles  defending champion, Oyinlomo Quadri expressively  beat her junior team mate Serena Teluwo 6-0, 6-0. The CBN Senior Tennis Championship main draw enters day three today with third round actions in both the Men’s and Women’s  event while the wheelchair category serves-off today as well.